{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/articles/tarsnap-bitbar","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"14576566-d863-5f05-b254-fbd4ba3d322f","html":"<p>I came across a really cool OSX menu bar library and thought it would be a really good solution to show my Tarsnap backup statuses.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/matryer/bitbar\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">github.com/matryer/bitbar</a></p>\n<p>I love how easy it is to write a plugin for BitBar in Ruby.</p>\n<p>It’s as simple as:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"ruby\"><pre class=\"language-ruby\"><code class=\"language-ruby\"><span class=\"token comment\">#!/usr/bin/ruby</span>\nputs <span class=\"token string\">\"Cool Menubar\"</span>\nputs <span class=\"token string\">\"---\"</span>\nputs <span class=\"token string\">\"The time is: <span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token delimiter tag\">#{</span><span class=\"token builtin\">Time</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>now<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>strftime<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'%T'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token delimiter tag\">}</span></span>\"</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>Anyway, I updated my git repo to include a BitBar plugin and also updated the main backup script to output a nice JSON file for it to read: <a href=\"https://github.com/aaronvb/tarsnap_backup\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">github.com/aaronvb/tarsnap_backup</a></p>\n<p>And here’s a screenshot of it in use:</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 570px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/432e7/bitbar_ss.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.66666666666666%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/8ac56/bitbar_ss.webp 240w,\n/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/d3be9/bitbar_ss.webp 480w,\n/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/048c8/bitbar_ss.webp 570w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/8ff5a/bitbar_ss.png 240w,\n/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/e85cb/bitbar_ss.png 480w,\n/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/432e7/bitbar_ss.png 570w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 570px) 100vw, 570px\"\n          type=\"image/png\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/3c2f61f3269749f6a011a22033444644/432e7/bitbar_ss.png\"\n          alt=\"bitbar_ss.png\"\n          title=\"bitbar_ss.png\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n          style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","fields":{"slug":"/articles/tarsnap-bitbar","tagSlugs":["/tag/code/","/tag/customize/","/tag/mac-os/","/tag/ruby/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2016-02-27","description":"BitBar support for automated Tarsnap backups with Ruby.","tags":["Code","Customize","macOS","Ruby"],"title":"BitBar, Tarsnap, and Ruby","legacyArticleId":null}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/articles/tarsnap-bitbar"}},"staticQueryHashes":["2255556206","251939775","401334301"]}